div.p:
Who euer runnes from his Colours, be hee native or forreiner;
and does not defend them to the vttermoſt of his power, ſo
long as they be in danger, ſhall ſuffer death for it.

Whoſoeuer preſuming to doe the ſame, & ſhalbe taken therewith;
ſhalbe proceeded withall like thoſe that flye out of the
Field. Their Goods alſo ſhalbe confiſcate.

In our Lower Court, they ſhall alſo hold the ſame order;
ſauing that the particular Court of euery Regiment, ſhall be
holden in their owne Quarter.
